+# Pala Token Intelligence
+
+## Purpose
+Token decisions for repository intake should be predictable, safe, and low-noise so local context stays controlled and useful.
+
+## Token Intake Rules
+- Start with project policy and core CLI files.
+- Classify every artifact before full read.
+- Prefer summaries for bulky or repetitive artifacts.
+- Keep generated, backup, and secret-bearing outputs out of normal session context.
+
+## Decision Classes
+- `READ_FULL`
+- `SUMMARY_ONLY`
+- `DO_NOT_READ`
+
+## File Policy
+| Pattern | Decision | Reason |
+|---|---|---|
+| `README.md` | `READ_FULL` | Project baseline and intent |
+| `INSTALL.md` | `READ_FULL` | Setup context |
+| `AGENTS.md` | `READ_FULL` | Operating rules |
+| `pala.py` | `READ_FULL` | Core CLI logic |
+| `dashboard/index.html` | `READ_FULL` | Dashboard behavior and cards |
+| `docs/*.md` | `SUMMARY_ONLY` | Policy docs usually need summary first |
+| `data/records/*` | `SUMMARY_ONLY` | Operational history index |
+| `data/reports/*` | `DO_NOT_READ` | Generated output artifacts |
+| `data/backups/*` | `DO_NOT_READ` | Backup package history |
+| `data/attachments/*` | `DO_NOT_READ` | Media/artifact-heavy data |
+
+## External Source Policy
+- New external repo: inspect metadata/docs/structure before code-level reading.
+- MCP/SDK candidates: index first, summary second.
+- Public docs/blogs: read summary-level unless a concrete snippet is required.
+
+## Dashboard Cards
+- Token Budget
+- Context Risk
+- Files Read
+- Files Blocked
+- Largest Token Sources
+- Recommended Next Read
+- Do Not Read
+- Prompt Cache Candidate: first candidate for compact, reusable context seed to reduce repeated cold reads.
+- Compaction Needed
+
+## Codex Prompt Discipline
+- Keep prompts small and task-scoped.
+- Use command outputs as evidence.
+- Stay within local, reproducible checks before broad reads.
+
+## Next Steps
+- Keep decision policy stable until acceptance criteria are validated.
+- Tune card thresholds only with clear evidence from repeated scans.

